- ## [Rock]
- Mm-hmm.

01:40.900 --> 01:43.130
## [Humming]

01:47.207 --> 01:49.107
- <i>[Marge] Breakfast!</i>
- [Whistling]

01:49.209 --> 01:51.177
Breakfast?
[Giggling]

01:56.149 --> 01:58.049
[Groans]
Cereal?

01:58.151 --> 02:01.052
You know I like my breakfast
fried or chicken-fried.

02:01.154 --> 02:04.351
It's a healthy cereal from Europe.
<i>MÃ¼eslix!</i>

02:04.457 --> 02:05.981
[All Shuddering]

02:06.092 --> 02:08.219
They also make <i>Juice-lix.</i>

02:08.328 --> 02:10.228
[Grunting]

02:10.330 --> 02:12.230
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>
- That's Milhouse.

02:12.332 --> 02:16.359
- <i>[Ringing Frantically]</i>
- And it sounds like he has big news!

02:16.469 --> 02:18.460
- Yech!
- [Groans]

02:18.571 --> 02:21.301
I'll get us out of this.
Say, Dad.

02:21.407 --> 02:24.467
Wanna go see my project
for the school science fair?

02:24.577 --> 02:26.636
No, Lisa.

02:26.746 --> 02:31.183
But I sure don't wanna
eat this crappy breakfast.

02:32.919 --> 02:34.682
[Snickers]

02:34.787 --> 02:38.848
Meet Linguo, the grammar robot.
I built him all by myself.

02:38.958 --> 02:41.654
If you misuse language,
he'll correct you.

02:41.761 --> 02:44.161
Well, let's put him to the test.

02:44.264 --> 02:46.562
Me love beer.

02:46.666 --> 02:48.429
<i>I love beer.</i>

02:48.535 --> 02:52.699
- Oh, he loves beer. Here, little fella.
- Dad, no!

02:52.805 --> 02:56.673
- Error.
- I'm sorry. I thought he was a party robot.

02:56.776 --> 02:59.336
Oh! This is why
I can't have nice things.

02:59.445 --> 03:03.279
[Groaning] Every time I design a robot,
somebody comes along and-

03:03.383 --> 03:06.113
- [Sniffing]
- ## [Humming]

03:06.219 --> 03:09.313
- Ooh! Can I have a brownie?
- They're for after dinner.

03:09.422 --> 03:14.223
- Ooh! Can I have dinner?
- You can't have a brownie, period.

03:14.327 --> 03:17.160
- <i>Homer wants a brownie. I'm gonna get one.</i>
- No.

03:17.263 --> 03:19.163
- Coming in from the left.
- Stop it.

03:19.265 --> 03:22.063
- Or is it the right? Look out for the reach-around!
- Homer!

03:22.168 --> 03:26.127
He shoots, he sc-
[Screams] My thumb!

03:26.239 --> 03:28.639
- Oh, God! Oh, God! Oh, God!
- I'm sorry! I'm so sorry!

03:28.741 --> 03:32.404
[Groaning] Sorry doesn't
put thumbs on the hand, Marge!

03:32.512 --> 03:35.845
Well, calm down. If we hurry,
they can reattach your thumb.

03:35.949 --> 03:38.383
Reattach a thumb?
This isn't <i>Gattaca!</i>

03:38.484 --> 03:40.384
- We've just gotta get your thumb to the-
- [Both Gasp]

03:40.486 --> 03:42.920
<i>Where did it go?</i>

03:43.022 --> 03:45.183
- [Gasps]
- [Growling]

03:45.291 --> 03:47.316
Okay, boy.
Drop the thumb.

03:47.427 --> 03:49.122
[Growling]

03:49.229 --> 03:52.289
Nobody's gonna tackle you.
[Grunts]

03:52.398 --> 03:54.696
D'oh!
Come back with my thumb!

03:56.936 --> 03:58.961
9-1-1.
This better be good.

03:59.072 --> 04:00.937
I cut off my husband's thumb.

04:01.040 --> 04:03.008
Attempted murder?

04:03.109 --> 04:05.942
You'll burn for this- burn in jail!

04:06.045 --> 04:10.141
- It was an accident!
- Yeah, yeah. Save it for <i>Dateline Tuesday.</i>

04:10.250 --> 04:12.775
Uh, what's your address
so I can come arrest you?

04:12.885 --> 04:15.547
Arrest me?
Um, my address...

04:15.655 --> 04:20.115
it's, um, 123 Fake Street.

04:20.226 --> 04:22.626
123 Fake Street.
Got it.

04:22.729 --> 04:25.095
- Come on! Come on, boy.
- [Barking]

04:25.198 --> 04:28.031
Oh, please give it back!

04:28.134 --> 04:30.568
You want people food?
I can get you people food.

04:30.670 --> 04:32.570
- [Barks]
- Oh!

04:32.672 --> 04:34.697
I have nothing he wants!

04:34.807 --> 04:38.334
And Harry Potter
and all his wizard friends...

04:38.444 --> 04:42.676
- went straight to hell for practicing witchcraft.
- Yea!

04:42.782 --> 04:45.580
- [Barks]
- What the diddlio?

04:45.685 --> 04:47.550
- Give me back my thumb!
- <i>[Barking]</i>

04:47.654 --> 04:48.712
- [Grunts]
- [Whimpers]

04:50.223 --> 04:52.987
[Whistle Tooting]

04:53.092 --> 04:55.026
[Gasps, Grunts]

04:55.128 --> 04:57.824
[Crying]

04:57.930 --> 04:59.591
[Marge]
We've gotta get to the hospital, Homer!

04:59.699 --> 05:02.600
Okay. If the doctor asks
why you cut it off...

05:02.702 --> 05:04.727
you caught me in bed
with four beautiful women.

05:04.837 --> 05:06.805
- Let's just say that Bart did it.
- <i>[Crash]</i>

05:08.207 --> 05:10.732
Oh, doodlebugs.

05:10.843 --> 05:14.904
My Ferrari!
I had to do awful things to pay for her.

05:16.082 --> 05:18.073
- [Grunts]
- Homer, help!

05:18.184 --> 05:20.846
<i>[Homer Whispering]</i>
<i>Marge! Over here!</i>

05:24.290 --> 05:26.986
- [Tires Screeching]
- [Yelling]

05:29.062 --> 05:32.088
[Door Sensor Dinging]

05:32.198 --> 05:36.396
I'm sorry, Homer.
Your H.M.O. Doesn't cover this type of injury.

05:36.502 --> 05:38.493
But I have finger insurance!

05:38.604 --> 05:42.005
- A thumb is not a finger.
- Isn't there anything you can do?

05:42.108 --> 05:45.305
Well, I could cut off the other thumb
for a sense of symmetry.

05:45.411 --> 05:46.810
Symmetry, eh?

05:46.913 --> 05:50.371
Hibbert's really losing it.
We're going to Dr. Nick's.

05:50.483 --> 05:53.418
We need more ice.
My thumb is fading fast!

05:54.987 --> 05:57.421
Quick!
Moe, Marge cut off my thumb!

05:57.523 --> 06:00.651
No problem. Just stick the old
eye gouger in the pickle brine.

06:00.760 --> 06:04.958
- That'll keep your thumb fresh and delicious.
- Thanks, Moe.

06:05.064 --> 06:07.624
Hey, ain't you gonna have a beer?

06:07.734 --> 06:11.670
Well, I really shouldn't,
what with my massive blood loss and all.

06:11.771 --> 06:14.638
Although I do like the occasional beer.

06:15.975 --> 06:18.603
Did you ever see that Blue Man Group?

06:18.711 --> 06:21.077
Total rip-off of the Smurfs.

06:21.180 --> 06:23.740
And the Smurfs-
They suck!

06:23.850 --> 06:26.751
[Sniffing]
Uh-oh. I smell gangrene.

06:26.853 --> 06:29.651
- We gotta wake him up.
- A little coffee'll do the trick.

06:30.790 --> 06:33.350
[Muttering]
What?

06:33.459 --> 06:35.552
I gotta get to Dr. Nick's!

06:37.063 --> 06:40.931
Where's Marge?
Oh, that is <i>so</i> rude.

06:41.033 --> 06:44.298
Oh! I know.
I'll hitchhike!

06:48.141 --> 06:50.006
Oh, why isn't this working?

06:50.109 --> 06:52.634
<i>## [Country On Car Stereo]</i>

06:56.282 --> 06:59.274
- Hey, thanks for stopping.
- T'ain't nothin'.

06:59.385 --> 07:01.979
You and me share
a common infirmity.

07:02.088 --> 07:06.024
If anyone ever tells you a hog
won't eat a finger, they's lyin'.

07:08.027 --> 07:10.222
- [Tires Screeching]
- [Clucking]

07:13.599 --> 07:16.159
Oh, crap!
It's on fire!

07:16.269 --> 07:20.035
Inflammable means flammable?
What a country!

07:20.139 --> 07:22.300
Can you drive me to
Shelbyville Hospital?

07:22.408 --> 07:24.933
- I reckon so. Hey!
- <i>[Tires Screeching]</i>

07:25.044 --> 07:27.808
Somebody done "stolded" my wheels!

07:27.914 --> 07:30.815
Thanks a lot.
Now I gotta walk to Shelbyville.

07:30.917 --> 07:33.511
[Horn Honking]

07:34.921 --> 07:37.014
[Moans]
It's too late.

07:40.393 --> 07:44.022
Well, old friend,
we always knew this day would come.

07:44.130 --> 07:46.223
Say good-bye to your brother.

07:46.332 --> 07:49.358
- [Explosion]
- What the hell!

07:50.670 --> 07:53.798
[Gasps]
Linguo... dead?

07:53.906 --> 07:56.067
Linguo...

07:56.175 --> 07:58.143
<i>is...</i>

07:58.244 --> 08:00.439
- dead.
- [Powering Off]

08:16.696 --> 08:19.062
Son of a diddly!

08:23.135 --> 08:25.467
## [New Age]

08:30.643 --> 08:32.543
<i>[Marge]</i>
<i>Breakfast!</i>

08:32.645 --> 08:34.544
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>
- That's Milhouse.

08:34.647 --> 08:38.707
- <i>[Ringing Frantically]</i>
- And it sounds like he has big news!

08:38.818 --> 08:40.876
- Yech!
- [Groans]

08:40.986 --> 08:43.649
I'll get us out of this.
Say, Dad.

08:43.756 --> 08:46.816
Wanna go see my project
for the school science fair?

08:46.926 --> 08:49.019
No, Lisa.

08:49.128 --> 08:53.189
But I sure don't wanna eat
this crappy breakfast.

08:55.334 --> 08:57.461
- Here, little fella.
- Dad, no!

08:57.570 --> 09:01.301
- Error.
- I'm sorry. I thought he was a party robot.

09:01.407 --> 09:03.932
Oh! This is why
I can't have nice things!

09:04.043 --> 09:06.136
[Groaning]

09:06.245 --> 09:08.873
- Every time I design a robot,
somebody comes along and-
- [Sniffing]

09:13.019 --> 09:16.978
Hang on, Linguo.
You'll be up and conjugating in no time.

09:17.089 --> 09:19.614
<i>[Homer Screams]</i>
<i>My thumb!</i>

09:19.725 --> 09:22.626
Quiet, please.
Some of us are trying to weld.

09:22.728 --> 09:24.992
Almost done.
Just lay still.

09:25.097 --> 09:28.362
- <i>Lie</i> still.
- I knew that. Just testing.

09:28.467 --> 09:29.764
Sentence fragment.

09:29.869 --> 09:33.464
"Sentence fragment"
is also a sentence fragment.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.474
- Must conserve battery power.
- [Powers Off]

09:36.576 --> 09:38.976
- Just come on.
- <i>[Horn Honking]</i>

09:39.078 --> 09:41.273
Uh-oh! The bus!

09:41.380 --> 09:43.575
Hey, stop! Wait!

09:43.683 --> 09:47.779
Oh! Any day but science project day!

09:47.887 --> 09:51.254
Kiss first place good-bye, Lisa!

09:51.357 --> 09:53.757
- [Sinister Laughter]
- [Electrical Crackling]

09:55.127 --> 09:57.027
Oh, no!

09:57.129 --> 09:59.962
Somebody took my bike!
[Groans]

10:00.066 --> 10:02.660
Mom, I need a ride to school!

10:02.768 --> 10:04.929
<i>[Marge]</i>
<i>We gotta get to the hospital, Homer!</i>

10:05.037 --> 10:07.005
[Groans]

10:17.583 --> 10:20.780
[Screams]

10:20.886 --> 10:23.116
Idiot!
You almost ran over a viewer!

10:23.222 --> 10:26.885
And she's in our key demo!
Sorry about that, kid. Need a ride?

10:26.993 --> 10:29.791
- Can you take me to school, Krusty?
- Hop in.

10:32.331 --> 10:35.357
Hey, moron.
Springfield Elementary, and step on it.

10:35.468 --> 10:38.301
[Chittering]

10:38.404 --> 10:40.429
<i>[Siren Wails]</i>

10:40.539 --> 10:43.667
Hey, Teeny, you know where
123 Fake Street is?

10:45.144 --> 10:49.012
Ah, it's okay.
Hey, we got the same hat.

10:50.449 --> 10:52.917
- Thanks, Mr. Teeny.
- <i>[Chitters]</i>

10:58.491 --> 11:02.552
- Wha-
- [Speaking French]

11:02.662 --> 11:05.130
[Repeating In French]

11:07.299 --> 11:09.995
Huh?
This isn't Miss Hoover's class.

11:10.102 --> 11:14.630
I do not know this Mademoiselle Hoover
of which you speak.

11:14.740 --> 11:17.038
What's happening?
Where am I?

11:17.143 --> 11:20.601
<i>Sacre bleu!</i>
What a foolish question!

11:20.713 --> 11:23.511
You are at
West Springfield Elementary School.

11:23.616 --> 11:26.642
<i>West</i> Springfield?

11:26.752 --> 11:29.084
I'm at the wrong school!

11:29.188 --> 11:32.919
- [All Laughing]
- <i>En FranÃ§ais.</i>

11:33.025 --> 11:35.152
[Haughty Laughter]

11:35.261 --> 11:37.491
[Gasps]
Sorry.

11:37.596 --> 11:39.791
I was rushing because
I'm in the wrong school.

11:39.899 --> 11:41.799
[Giggles]
Can you believe that?

11:41.901 --> 11:46.270
It's understandable. All the schools in
this area were built from identical plans.

11:46.372 --> 11:49.432
I guess they didn't have
enough money to hire I.M. Pei.

11:49.542 --> 11:52.909
Oh. You know about I.M. Pei?

11:53.012 --> 11:54.912
I am impressed.

11:55.014 --> 11:58.245
[Nerdy Laughter]

11:58.350 --> 12:00.648
- My name's Thelonious.
- As in Monk?

12:00.753 --> 12:03.847
Yes. The esoteric appeal
is worth the beatings.

12:03.956 --> 12:07.221
- What do your friends call you?
- I don't really have any friends.

12:07.326 --> 12:10.420
[Gasps]
Just like me!

12:11.831 --> 12:14.698
<i>## [Pop]</i>

12:19.705 --> 12:21.673
Oh, my God!

12:21.774 --> 12:25.335
It's 11:15!
We've been spinning for hours.

12:25.444 --> 12:28.470
I've got to get to my school
and hand in Linguo.

12:28.581 --> 12:30.845
Oh, but I don't want to leave you.

12:30.950 --> 12:34.249
You must.
You can't sacrifice grades for romance.

12:34.353 --> 12:37.151
- That's not the girl I fell for.
- Will I ever see you again?

12:37.256 --> 12:40.953
Of course you will...
at the magnet high school. Now, go.

12:44.330 --> 12:46.764
[Panting]

12:46.866 --> 12:48.766
Hmm. It's noon.

12:48.868 --> 12:51.132
That's about when Dad
gets the brew shakes.

12:53.405 --> 12:56.431
My dad's not here?
I need a ride to school!

12:56.542 --> 12:58.908
- Yeah, yeah. We all got problems.
- [Whimpering]

12:59.011 --> 13:02.970
Chief Wiggum, can you drive me to school?
It's an emergency!

13:03.082 --> 13:06.142
No can do, doll face.
I got an informant wearing a wire.

13:06.252 --> 13:08.777
[Chuckles]
Just like on <i>Nash Bridges.</i>

13:08.888 --> 13:11.322
- We're trying to get the goods on some smugglers.
- [Frequency Whirring]

13:11.423 --> 13:14.950
[Fat Tony] Why, I'd be delighted
to sell you some illegally smuggled goods.

13:15.060 --> 13:18.757
- That sounds like Fat Tony.
- Only one way to be sure.

13:18.864 --> 13:21.025
Fat Tony, is that you?
Fat Tony?

13:21.133 --> 13:22.964
[Man]
Hey, where's that voice coming from?

13:23.068 --> 13:25.662
- [Man #2] This guy's wearing a wire!
- [Fat Tony] Take him out!

13:25.771 --> 13:27.796
[Gunfire]

13:27.907 --> 13:30.774
My bad.
I can't work my answering machine either.

13:30.876 --> 13:33.367
[Chuckles]
Now I need a new informant.

13:33.479 --> 13:36.346
Say, Lisa, people trust you.
How would you like to be a snitch?

13:36.448 --> 13:38.643
The pay stinks, but-

13:38.751 --> 13:40.343
Oh.

13:40.452 --> 13:42.420
Quick!
Moe, Marge cut off my thumb!

13:46.091 --> 13:48.025
- <i>[Horn Honking]</i>
- Lisa!

13:48.127 --> 13:50.493
Mom, where'd you get that car?

13:50.596 --> 13:53.724
I stole it from McBain after
I cut off your father's thumb.

13:53.833 --> 13:55.733
Can you take me to school, please?

13:55.835 --> 13:57.860
Not right now.
Your father's in there, and-

13:57.970 --> 14:00.905
<i>[Homer]</i>
<i>Did you ever see that Blue Man Group?</i>

14:01.006 --> 14:03.065
Oh, he's on the Blue Man Group again.

14:03.175 --> 14:05.166
Come on.
We've got lots of time.

14:11.050 --> 14:13.450
- [Engine Sputters, Stalls]
- Oh, no!

14:13.552 --> 14:18.785
We're out of gas. I couldn't figure out
this stupid Italian gas gauge.

14:18.891 --> 14:20.882
I've gotta get to school!

14:20.993 --> 14:23.427
## [Country On Car Stereo]

14:23.529 --> 14:26.726
Hmm.
Let's hitch a ride with that hick.

14:31.170 --> 14:33.400
Abracathumbra!

14:33.505 --> 14:33.971
[Laughing]

14:34.073 --> 14:37.236
Dang! You could be
one of them TV magic queers.

14:43.782 --> 14:45.249
- [Tires Screeching]
- [Clucking]

14:45.351 --> 14:47.012
[Both Yell]

14:48.354 --> 14:52.347
- Shoo!
- Mom, I have to get to school! It's 10 to 3:00!

14:54.126 --> 14:57.653
Well, I've already borrowed one car.
Let's go!

14:59.498 --> 15:02.262
Somebody done "stolded" my wheels.

15:09.074 --> 15:12.043
Thanks a lot!
Now I gotta walk to Shelbyville.

15:12.144 --> 15:13.475
There's the school!

15:13.579 --> 15:14.910
First place, here I come.

15:15.014 --> 15:17.312
[Gasps]
Look out!

15:17.416 --> 15:18.610
- Bart!
- <i>[Tires Screeching]</i>

15:18.717 --> 15:20.947
[Gasps, Screams]

15:33.132 --> 15:35.498
Son of a diddly!

15:39.571 --> 15:42.734
Hey, hey! Hey, hey!
Hey, hey!

15:42.841 --> 15:45.867
Lazy, eh?
Get him, boys!

15:45.978 --> 15:47.878
- ## [Theme]
- Wake up! Wake up! Wake up!

15:47.980 --> 15:49.948
Okay, okay!

15:52.685 --> 15:54.585
<i>[Marge]</i>
<i>Breakfast!</i>

15:54.687 --> 15:56.587
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>
- That's Milhouse.

15:56.689 --> 16:01.388
- <i>[Ringing Frantically]</i>
- And it sounds like he has big news!

16:03.462 --> 16:07.023
- I found something awesome in the woods!
- Is it a dead body?

16:07.132 --> 16:10.465
- It's cooler than a million dead bodies!
- [Snickers]

16:10.569 --> 16:12.434
You take my sister's bike.

16:13.939 --> 16:15.804
Let's see.
Front door. Back door.

16:15.908 --> 16:18.308
Skinner's. Flanders'.
Your house.

16:18.410 --> 16:20.401
Ah! Lisa's bike.

16:23.515 --> 16:27.383
- What's it like riding a girl's bike?
- It's disturbingly comfortable.

16:31.790 --> 16:34.623
Whoa! How'd you find it?

16:34.727 --> 16:38.629
- This is where I come to cry.
- Cool.

16:41.800 --> 16:44.064
Wow! Sacks!

16:44.169 --> 16:48.435
- Burlap sacks!
- It gets better. They're full of fireworks!

16:49.742 --> 16:52.108
Bottle rockets, frog launchers,
Weeping Mamas.

16:52.211 --> 16:54.372
Tijuana Toilet Crackers!

16:54.480 --> 16:57.711
<i>[Bart]</i>
<i>Three, two, one. Gnomes, blow up.</i>

16:58.984 --> 17:02.044
[Both Laughing Hysterically]

17:06.224 --> 17:08.250
[Grunting Loudly]

17:08.359 --> 17:10.954
- [High-pitched Screaming]
- We're not ready!

17:11.063 --> 17:13.031
[Sinister Chuckle]

17:14.133 --> 17:16.032
- [Grunts]
- Uh-oh.

17:18.069 --> 17:21.528
So what are we doing,
a lengthening or a widening?

17:21.640 --> 17:24.404
Yarr.
Uh, let's make it both.

17:24.510 --> 17:27.968
- Garr!
- Don't worry. It's <i>inflammable.</i>

17:29.848 --> 17:32.612
Let's keep this our little secret.

17:32.718 --> 17:36.210
- <i>[Siren Wailing]</i>
- We gotta hide!

17:37.322 --> 17:39.517
We'll be safe in here.

17:44.897 --> 17:47.058
Here we are.
123 Fake Street.

17:47.166 --> 17:49.259
The home of Knifey Wifey.

17:49.368 --> 17:52.235
Hey, Chief, can I hold my gun sideways?
It looks so cool.

17:52.337 --> 17:54.305
[Chuckling]
Ah, sure.

17:54.406 --> 17:56.340
Whatever you want, birthday boy.

17:58.143 --> 18:00.634
Okay, drop the knife, Stabitha!

18:00.746 --> 18:03.442
- [Both Grunt]
- Great grilled-cheese ghost!

18:03.549 --> 18:06.040
We've uncovered
a hard-core cracker house.

18:06.151 --> 18:08.016
There's enough Chinese sky candy here...

18:08.120 --> 18:10.554
to put you boys away for a long time.

18:10.656 --> 18:14.615
I can't go to juvie.
They use guys like me as currency!

18:14.726 --> 18:17.490
Yeah. They'll pass you around like-

18:17.596 --> 18:19.496
Well, like currency, like you said.

18:19.598 --> 18:21.498
Maybe we can make you boys a deal.

18:24.470 --> 18:26.802
Your mission is to find
the fireworks smugglers...

18:26.905 --> 18:30.102
and get them to say
something incriminating on this tape.

18:30.209 --> 18:32.473
"Hootie and the Blowfish"?

18:32.578 --> 18:34.478
Yeah.
It's cheaper than blank tape.

18:35.581 --> 18:38.175
Great idea to smuggle fireworks, boss.

18:38.283 --> 18:40.376
Yeah, I was gettin' sick
of running those unions.

18:40.486 --> 18:42.454
So much paperwork.

18:42.554 --> 18:44.283
<i>Knock-knock.</i>
<i>Excuse me.</i>

18:44.389 --> 18:47.950
My friend and I were interested
in purchasing quality fireworks.

18:48.060 --> 18:49.925
Yes, we are.

18:50.028 --> 18:54.226
Why, I'd be delighted to sell you
some illegally smuggled goods.

18:54.333 --> 18:57.427
<i>[Wiggum On Radio]</i>
<i>Fat Tony, is that you? Fat Tony?</i>

18:57.536 --> 19:00.801
- Hey, where's that voice coming from?
- This guy's wearin' a wire!

19:00.906 --> 19:03.067
Take him out!

19:03.175 --> 19:05.075
[Grunting]

19:05.177 --> 19:07.543
Whoa!

19:07.646 --> 19:10.114
- [Wiggum] My bad.
- [Grunts]

19:15.888 --> 19:17.879
<i>Hey, there they are!</i>

19:17.990 --> 19:20.891
- Gentlemen, remove your guns from your holsters.
- Shoulder or ankle?

19:20.993 --> 19:23.791
Surprise me.

19:23.896 --> 19:26.330
- [Both Whimpering]
- [Groaning]

19:28.634 --> 19:30.534
Milhouse, quick!

19:32.671 --> 19:34.969
[Gasps]
Look out!

19:35.073 --> 19:38.565
- Bart!
- [Gasps, Screams]

19:38.677 --> 19:40.235
[Clunks]

19:40.345 --> 19:43.837
- Ow! Mom!
- <i>[Milhouse] Hurry up, Bart!</i>

19:57.229 --> 19:59.322
<i>[Tires Screeching]</i>

19:59.431 --> 20:00.989
[Both Panting, Gasping]

20:01.099 --> 20:02.794
You ain't goin' nowhere!

20:02.901 --> 20:06.359
You leave those boys alone!

20:06.471 --> 20:08.996
- [Grunts]
- [Yelling]

20:10.275 --> 20:12.300
Hey, they's throwin' robots!

20:12.411 --> 20:15.209
They <i>are</i> throwing robots.

20:15.314 --> 20:18.010
He's disrespecting us.
Shutuppayouface!

20:18.116 --> 20:20.550
Shut up <i>your</i> face.

20:20.652 --> 20:23.382
- What's-a matta, you?
- You ain't so big.

20:23.488 --> 20:25.513
Me and him are gonna
whack you in the labonza!

20:25.624 --> 20:29.720
[Stammering]
Bad grammar overload!

20:29.828 --> 20:32.763
Error! Error!

20:32.864 --> 20:35.992
- [Explosion]
- What the hell!

20:37.202 --> 20:40.330
[Gasps]
Linguo... dead?

20:43.542 --> 20:46.375
<i>[Both Shuddering]</i>

20:46.478 --> 20:48.412
It's all right, boys.

20:48.513 --> 20:50.845
Oh, thank goodness everyone's okay.

20:50.949 --> 20:53.850
Except your thumb,
and Lisa's science project.

20:53.952 --> 20:56.978
I couldn't help but notice
your respective predicaments.

20:57.089 --> 21:01.116
Perhaps I may offer
a bipartite solution.

21:05.497 --> 21:07.431
There you go.
Enjoy your thumb.

21:07.532 --> 21:09.432
<i>[Lisa]</i>
<i>As the circulation returns...</i>

21:09.534 --> 21:13.368
the subject prepares
for a long and painful recovery.

21:15.440 --> 21:18.534
It's lucky for me that Legs
was an experienced Mob doctor.

21:18.644 --> 21:23.411
He once pulled a slug out of my arm
and inserted it into a stoolie's brain.

21:23.515 --> 21:25.506
That's a first place science project, Lisa.

21:25.617 --> 21:27.084
[All Cheering]

21:29.154 --> 21:33.523
Boy, this sure was one crazy day.

21:33.625 --> 21:36.025
- Right, Mr. Teeny?
- [Chuckling]

21:36.128 --> 21:39.120
[All Laughing]

21:39.231 --> 21:42.098
[Chittering Loudly]

22:27.579 --> 22:29.911
- [Laughter]
- <i>[French Teacher]</i> En FranÃ§ais.

